  "doc_id": "56889",
  "text": "The visible mould level was found to be higher than the level reported from a self-reported NZ telephone survey [CITATION_1] . The results showed that the visible mould level and the RH level were positively correlated and that the visible mould level and the temperature were negatively correlated. These findings are consistent with a higher percentage of visible mould detected in households where UGHs were operated. Garrett et al. [CITATION_2] reported a correlation between evidence of dampness and visible mould. Another study found fungal levels were positively correlated with basement humidity [CITATION_3] and negative correlation was found between the temperature of the room and the fungal level [CITATION_4] .",
